documentation.text: Used to delegate ownership of a contract to another address, to save on unneeded transactions to approve contract use for users

@title ERC721Tradable
 ERC721Tradable - ERC721 contract that whitelists a trading address, and has minting functionality.

We rely on the OZ Counter util to keep track of the next available ID.
 We track the nextTokenId instead of the currentTokenId to save users on gas costs. 
 Read more about it here: https://shiny.mirror.xyz/OUampBbIz9ebEicfGnQf5At_ReMHlZy0tB4glb9xQ0E

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct Counters.Counter storage pointer) view returns (uint256)

documentation.text:
@dev Mints a token to an address with a tokenURI.
 @param _to address of the future owner of the token

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct Counters.Counter storage pointer) view returns (uint256)

documentation.text:
@dev Returns the total tokens minted so far.
1 is always subtracted from the Counter since it tracks the next available tokenId.
Override isApprovedForAll to whitelist user's OpenSea proxy accounts to enable gas-less listings.
This is used instead of msg.sender as transactions won't be sent by the original token owner, but by OpenSea.
Used to delegate ownership of a contract to another address, to save on unneeded transactions to approve contract use for users
